# Padroes de Estado Flutter

## ChangeNotifier

```dart
class CounterNotifier extends ChangeNotifier {
  int _count = 0;
  int get count => _count;

  void increment() {
    _count++;
    notifyListeners();
  }

  void decrement() {
    if (_count > 0) {
      _count--;
      notifyListeners();
    }
  }
}
```

## ValueNotifier

```dart
final counterNotifier = ValueNotifier<int>(0);

// No widget:
ValueListenableBuilder<int>(
  valueListenable: counterNotifier,
  builder: (context, value, child) {
    return Text('$value');
  },
);
```

## Provider

```dart
// Registro
MultiProvider(
  providers: [
    ChangeNotifierProvider(create: (_) => CounterNotifier()),
    ChangeNotifierProvider(create: (_) => AuthNotifier()),
  ],
  child: const MyApp(),
);

// Consumo
final counter = context.watch<CounterNotifier>();   // rebuild on change
final auth = context.read<AuthNotifier>();           // read once
context.select<CounterNotifier, int>((n) => n.count); // granular
```

## Riverpod

```dart
// Providers
final counterProvider = StateNotifierProvider<CounterNotifier, int>(
  (ref) => CounterNotifier(),
);

final userProvider = FutureProvider<User>((ref) async {
  final repository = ref.watch(userRepositoryProvider);
  return repository.fetchCurrentUser();
});

// Consumo no widget
class HomeScreen extends ConsumerWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    final count = ref.watch(counterProvider);
    final userAsync = ref.watch(userProvider);

    return userAsync.when(
      data: (user) => Text('${user.name}: $count'),
      loading: () => const CircularProgressIndicator(),
      error: (e, _) => Text('Erro: $e'),
    );
  }
}
```

## BLoC Pattern

```dart
// Eventos
sealed class CounterEvent {}
class Increment extends CounterEvent {}
class Decrement extends CounterEvent {}

// BLoC
class CounterBloc extends Bloc<CounterEvent, int> {
  CounterBloc() : super(0) {
    on<Increment>((event, emit) => emit(state + 1));
    on<Decrement>((event, emit) => emit(state - 1));
  }
}

// Consumo
BlocBuilder<CounterBloc, int>(
  builder: (context, count) => Text('$count'),
);
```

## Convencoes

- `ChangeNotifier` para estado simples e local
- `Riverpod` ou `Provider` para injecao de dependencias
- `BLoC` para fluxos de eventos complexos
- Nunca acessar estado diretamente, sempre via getters
- `notifyListeners` apenas apos mutacao real
- Separar notifiers por dominio (auth, cart, profile)
